<section id="metaphor-insight" class="py-24 sm:py-32">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <!-- Lead-in — flows from Hero's "SLOPE changes that" -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16" data-reveal>
      <p class="text-emerald text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">The Core Idea</p>
      <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-3xl sm:text-4xl mb-4">
        Give your agent a vocabulary it can actually use.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Sprint data is useless without context. Metaphors add the context — difficulty, risk, patterns, trajectory — in language that sticks.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Beat 1: Name the friction -->
    <div class="mb-8" data-reveal>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-6 sm:p-8">
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg leading-relaxed">
          When an agent reports <span class="text-text-muted font-mono text-base">"Sprint done, 4 tickets delivered, 1 bug"</span> — what did you learn?
        </p>
        <p class="text-text-muted mt-3 leading-relaxed">
          Nothing about difficulty. Nothing about whether the approach was right. Nothing about whether the same bug will happen next time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Beat 2: Introduce the unlock -->
    <div class="mb-8" data-reveal>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald/20 bg-bg-surface p-6 sm:p-8">
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg leading-relaxed">
          But when an agent reports <span class="text-emerald font-mono text-base">"Par 4, scored 4 — one bunker on the third shot, miss pattern trending long"</span> — suddenly you know:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-text-muted">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-emerald mt-1 shrink-0">&#8226;</span>
            <span>Difficulty was moderate</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-emerald mt-1 shrink-0">&#8226;</span>
            <span>Execution matched expectations</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-emerald mt-1 shrink-0">&#8226;</span>
            <span>There's a recurring issue with a name</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-emerald mt-1 shrink-0">&#8226;</span>
            <span>The team tends to over-scope</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Beat 3: The twist — sets up SeeItInAction -->
    <div class="mb-12" data-reveal>
      <p class="text-center text-text-secondary text-xl sm:text-2xl font-heading leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        And if golf isn't how your team thinks?<br />
        <span class="text-text-muted text-lg">The scoring engine doesn't change. Only the language does.</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Mapping visual: dev concept → metaphor layer → what you gain -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 sm:gap-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto" data-stagger>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-bg-card p-3 sm:p-4">
          <p class="text-text-muted text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Dev Concept</p>
          <p class="text-text-primary text-sm sm:text-base font-heading font-bold">Sprint</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-[10px] sm:text-xs mt-2">What you're doing</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-emerald/20 bg-emerald/5 p-3 sm:p-4">
          <p class="text-emerald text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Metaphor</p>
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="mx-auto mb-1 text-emerald/60" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
          </svg>
          <p class="text-emerald text-sm sm:text-base font-heading font-bold">Hole · Level · Encounter</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-[10px] sm:text-xs mt-2">How you frame it</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-bg-card p-3 sm:p-4">
          <p class="text-text-muted text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">You Gain</p>
          <p class="text-text-primary text-sm sm:text-base font-heading font-bold">Context</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-[10px] sm:text-xs mt-2">What makes it stick</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
